Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.47,0:00:02.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Mansion of Hope...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.97,0:00:07.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Once upon a time, it housed six talented young people.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.10,0:00:09.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, three years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.31,0:00:12.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One woman among the six died of a heart attack inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.94,0:00:16.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Instead of "Hope," people now call it the "Mansion of Death."
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.57,0:00:20.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that mansion, a new tragedy took place.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.24,0:00:24.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The deceased woman's husband, Akashi Shuusaku{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.66,0:00:28.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Had been confined to one of the mansion's\Nrooms, causing him to die of starvation.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.91,0:00:34.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In his final hours, Akashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} painted one\Nof the walls in the room bloody red.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.71,0:00:37.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What was he trying to say?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.01,0:00:43.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We deduced that our suspect is among the\Nremaining four who also resided in the mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.14,0:00:50.10,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,The rival of Inspector Yamato from Nagano Police,\NMorofushi Takaaki, took us with him on his investigation.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.14,0:00:48.14,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\fad(0,0)}Morofushi Takaaki (35)\NNagano Prefecture Arano Station Inspector
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.93,0:00:54.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We felt suspicious towards one Naoki Shirou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s reactions.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.15,0:01:00.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And so we revisited his apartment the next\Nday, only to find Naoki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} murdered.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.74,0:01:06.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Similar to Akashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, he was seated\Non a chair, facing a wall painted red.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.70,0:01:12.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The differences are that Naoki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s body\Nwas not seated on a chair painted white...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.00,0:01:15.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And there was no black chair in the room...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.79,0:01:21.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, the fact that instead of the victim, the\Nwall was seemingly painted by the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.09,0:01:24.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was the culprit challenging the police?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.68,0:01:26.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Or...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.72,0:01:30.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Love is magic, attack the mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.80,0:01:33.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On Saturday nights, be sure to click on Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.46,0:01:35.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit has assaulted Inspector Koumei!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.44,0:01:37.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can we finally solve the mystery of the Red Wall?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.83,0:01:39.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perceiving the one and only truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.44,0:01:41.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The appearance of a child and the intellect of an adult...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.32,0:01:43.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His name is: Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.21,0:03:31.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Regardless, if you don't want him to investigate\Nrashly alone, why don't you just go with him?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.43,0:03:35.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I bet you wanted to monitor him, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.35,0:03:41.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even yesterday when we went with Inspector Morofushi to\Nquestion those suspects, a strange car was following us.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.82,0:03:45.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was an officer's car, no?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.07,0:03:46.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.86,0:03:50.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, why monitor him?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.45,0:03:56.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We just told you that those three knew about\Nthe red wall at the crime scene, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.16,0:04:02.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But of course that information was also known to us police.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.29,0:04:09.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As such, since we know someone who was friends with Kobashi\NAoi is in the police force, shouldn't we take a closer look?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.26,0:04:11.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.47,0:04:15.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that Morofushi Takaaki...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.97,0:04:18.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's also one of the suspects!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.82,0:04:32.53,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\fad(0,0)}Midorikawa Naoki (38)\NActor
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.25,0:04:30.44,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Shiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} is...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.45,0:04:32.53,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Is that true!?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.07,0:04:39.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why we wanted to ask, last night between\N10:00 and 11:00, what were you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.58,0:04:45.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,During that time, I was in my room\Nreading my script for a TV drama.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.71,0:04:50.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I was done and went to sleep, it\Nwas about 2:00 in the morning I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.09,0:04:54.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, don't tell me you're suspecting me?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.39,0:04:58.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're asking just in case, and is there anyone who can support that?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.10,0:05:01.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My wife went to sleep at 9:00, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.52,0:05:05.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, if it's your spouse, their testimony won't count.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.98,0:05:10.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, did you notice anything about Shirou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.49,0:05:12.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like his being afraid of something.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.45,0:05:18.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I haven't seen him for a longtime, but\Nit seems Shuusaku met with him often.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.74,0:05:21.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s band wasn't doing very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.33,0:05:26.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shuusaku said he always came to visit and borrow money.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.92,0:05:34.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're asking me what I was doing\Nbetween 10:00 and 11:00 last night?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.68,0:05:38.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh please, don't tell me you, too, are\Nsuspecting me of Shiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s death?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.18,0:05:40.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By "you too," you mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.86,0:05:46.16,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\fad(250,250)}Yamabuki Shouji (39)\NFashion Designer
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.87,0:05:46.84,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,The officer from last night with slanted eyes and a small\Nmustache asked me the same thing, so I told him:
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.90,0:05:50.58,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,"I was in here alone working on my design. Is that problem?"
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.32,0:05:54.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that bastard Koumei has been here already, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.65,0:05:56.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Koumei"?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.53,0:05:59.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was that officer's name Koumei?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.58,0:06:04.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His nickname is Koumei, and he was a\Nclassmate of the Kobashi Aoi you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.17,0:06:08.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, he's the famous detective from Ao{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}'s book?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.88,0:06:13.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, about that Naoki Shirou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, had\Nanything happened to him recently?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.05,0:06:17.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Beats me—I'd heard he had some financial trouble, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.39,0:06:21.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, he did tell me he wanted to travel overseas!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.56,0:06:25.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I even asked him, "No problem with your traveling expenses?" too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.52,0:06:30.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez, the police again?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.23,0:06:36.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've said this before, during 10:00 and 1:00 last night\NI was sleeping on the sofa in the next room.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.53,0:06:39.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So Koumei's been here, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.53,0:06:42.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, do you have someone to verify that?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.30,0:06:47.50,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\fad(250,0)}Momose Takuto (37)\NCG Creator
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.49,0:06:47.50,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Go ask my partner who tried to wake me\Nup every hour starting from 11:00!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.75,0:06:54.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, but I covered myself with a blanket to sleep, so\Nthey likely couldn't tell if it was really me or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.42,0:07:00.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, about the murdered Naoki Shirou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},\Nhad anything suspicious happened to him?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.14,0:07:05.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who knows... a while back he came\Nto me specifically asking for money.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.64,0:07:09.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After I shooed him off angrily, he never came back.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.15,0:07:13.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, it seems like he got some money.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.07,0:07:16.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Looks like he was planning to go to Lecce in Italy.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.61,0:07:20.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He even e-mailed me saying, "If I'm gone, try searching there."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.28,0:07:22.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Lecce in Italy?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.04,0:07:26.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the way, that officer with slanted eyes and a small mustache...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.71,0:07:31.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was he really the model for the famous detective in Ao{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}'s book?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.25,0:07:33.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, but why do you ask?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.63,0:07:39.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A while ago, Yamabuki phoned me about it,\Nand said that Midori was surprised, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.10,0:07:47.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, we've finished hearing the three suspects talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.81,0:07:50.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But those three apparently had no alibis.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.85,0:07:54.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, looks like we have to solve\Nthe Red Wall mystery no matter what.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.53,0:07:57.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Red Wall...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.70,0:08:05.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that truly was a dying message by Akashi\NShuusaku{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, why did he paint the wall red?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.12,0:08:11.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's understandable why he didn't\Njust write out the culprit's name, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.97,0:08:26.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, he didn't write the culprit's name because...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.31,0:08:35.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He feared that, after he had passed on from starving, the culprit\Nwould return, discover it before anyone else, and remove it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.53,0:08:38.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Remove...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.69,0:08:39.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Red...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.88,0:08:40.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wall...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.05,0:08:41.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wall...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.03,0:09:06.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.95,0:09:31.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In this murder adaptation, Koumei is of no use.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.04,0:09:34.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's time for your early retirement.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.75,0:09:38.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What!?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.92,0:09:40.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Koumei disappeared!?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.80,0:09:42.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What were you doing, Uehara?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.22,0:09:43.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.26,0:09:46.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When we reached Gojou Forest, his car accelerated suddenly...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.35,0:09:48.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Gojou Forest?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.64,0:09:50.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's the forest where the mansion is!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.27,0:09:52.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Koumei should be headed there!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.23,0:09:54.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Go there now!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.35,0:09:54.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.36,0:09:58.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Koumei sent me a message?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.78,0:10:01.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe he figured out who the culprit is?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.95,0:10:04.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.74,0:10:05.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What was written in it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.33,0:10:10.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The late... Koumei...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.95,0:10:14.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey, don't jinx him.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.12,0:10:19.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Uehara, have you found Koumei yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.63,0:10:20.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.00,0:10:23.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've arrived at the mansion, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.97,0:10:28.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's on fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.26,0:10:29.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That Mansion of Death!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.10,0:10:31.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What!?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.27,0:10:32.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The mansion's on fire!?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.19,0:10:36.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And Koumei?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.60,0:10:37.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where's Koumei!?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.94,0:10:39.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.73,0:10:41.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His car is in front of the mansion, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.32,0:10:45.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the time I got here, the mansion was already burning!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.07,0:10:48.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Koumei, can it be...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.78,0:10:51.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They've struck first again...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.04,0:10:53.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector Morofushi!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.31,0:11:15.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Koumei!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.15,0:11:19.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If he's still inside, it's too late...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.98,0:11:21.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.53,0:11:29.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Once I discover the truth, I promise I'll contact you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.49,0:11:34.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Koumei, I haven't... gotten your report yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.45,0:11:36.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shit!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.46,0:11:37.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait, you!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.21,0:11:39.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stop it, Inspector Yamato!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.92,0:11:42.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no use entering now!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.88,0:11:43.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.84,0:11:45.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We won't know if we don't find out!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.30,0:11:48.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like—I—said!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.80,0:11:52.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's meaningless to enter the mansion, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.97,0:11:54.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Koumei!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.56,0:12:01.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, what happened!?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.56,0:12:03.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I entered the back door where the fire hadn't spread...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.73,0:12:06.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And found him lying in that room!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.90,0:12:10.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Looks like someone assaulted him.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.20,0:12:11.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who was it, Koumei?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.41,0:12:12.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who did this to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.83,0:12:16.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No use, he's completely unconscious.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.50,0:12:19.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Moreover, the trauma is on the back of his head.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.71,0:12:22.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If he was hit from behind, it's unlikely he saw the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.50,0:12:27.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, the culprit can be anyone among the people over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.01,0:12:31.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, why are you guys here?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.05,0:12:33.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, no...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.14,0:12:35.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We were called over...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.01,0:12:36.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With this text message...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.14,0:12:38.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Text message?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.48,0:12:40.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who sent it!?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.69,0:12:43.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's from you, Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.02,0:12:43.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.40,0:12:50.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It says, "Come to the mansion where Shuusaku\Nwas trapped, I have things to check with you."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.61,0:12:51.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.95,0:12:54.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it was at 14:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.24,0:12:57.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then we came here and saw it burning.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.95,0:13:01.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't you think it's odd that I would send you text messages?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.33,0:13:04.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I felt strange for a bit, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.09,0:13:08.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I called these two, they said they received the same message.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.96,0:13:13.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The contents and the address were the\Nsame, so we didn't suspect anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.76,0:13:15.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So did you three come here together?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.39,0:13:19.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, we were told to come alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.31,0:13:20.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the text.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.91,0:13:35.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Naoki Shirou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s cell phone?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.62,0:13:39.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The text message was sent to those three from that phone?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.24,0:13:39.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.45,0:13:46.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After killing Naoki Shirou, the culprit probably\Nswiped the phone and changed the mailing address.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.54,0:13:50.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He then sent the same message to\Nthe three suspects, himself included.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.88,0:13:52.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.51,0:13:54.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The suspicious individuals are...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.84,0:14:00.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Midorikawa Naoki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, Yamabuki Shouji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},\Nand Momose Takuto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, these three.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.18,0:14:03.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If the culprit manages to drag the other two over...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.31,0:14:08.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit wouldn't be the only one without\Nan alibi when the mansion is burned down.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.98,0:14:11.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why did they have to light it on fire?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.19,0:14:13.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit figured it out, didn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.24,0:14:18.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That the dying message of the red wall left by Akashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.91,0:14:21.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Actually pointed out who the culprit was!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.83,0:14:25.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So the culprit went there intending to burn down the mansion, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.04,0:14:32.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Unfortunately Koumei was there, so they had no choice but to\Nknock him out, and try to burn him to ashes with the mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.01,0:14:35.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.05,0:14:37.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's the meaning behind the red wall?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.64,0:14:39.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You already know, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.14,0:14:41.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It'd be nice if I figured that out...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.10,0:14:43.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Killing move...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.81,0:14:46.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,DRILL PUNCH!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.94,0:14:48.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.27,0:14:51.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You don't even know the truth, so just shut your trap!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.32,0:14:58.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, even though our first crime scene went\Ninto flames, we did receive a new clue.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.37,0:15:03.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That Koumei sent me a text message.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.37,0:15:07.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"The late Koumei."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.04,0:15:12.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, didn't the culprit send that to Kan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} on purpose?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.00,0:15:13.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't think that's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.88,0:15:19.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The message was interrupted half way, and he did say that\Nhe'd contact Inspector Yamato after he solved the mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.64,0:15:23.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, apparently Inspector Morofushi realized something...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.81,0:15:28.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And while he was in the process of texting it to\NInspector Yamato, he was struck down by the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.73,0:15:32.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I bet he pressed the send button just before he passed out.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.65,0:15:35.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why during it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.20,0:15:41.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The famous tactician Shokatsu Koumei and Inspector Morofushi\NTakaaki's having a nickname that sounds like "Koumei"...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.91,0:15:43.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wasn't the culprit just utilizing that reference?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.20,0:15:46.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just to tell us, "Koumei is dead."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.46,0:15:49.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"The late Koumei scares away the living Zhonda."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.79,0:15:50.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.83,0:15:51.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.75,0:15:58.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The army led by Shokatsuryou Koumei in the Shu\NKingdom appeared to be retreating from battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.22,0:16:05.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Seeing that and assuming Koumei had died of illness, the\NWei Kingdom's tactician Sima Yi Zhonda ordered a pursuit.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.23,0:16:12.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the Shu army, following Koumei's final words,\Npretended to be ready for a counterattack.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.40,0:16:19.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That made Zhonda scream "Koumei isn't dead; we're\Nfalling into their trap!" and immediately retreated.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.45,0:16:26.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Basically, the moral is: "People can have a great\Ninfluence and intimidate the living, even after death."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.66,0:16:34.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But in that case, the "late Koumei" would\Nrefer to the starved Akashi Shuusaku{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.21,0:16:36.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the "living Zhonda" would mean the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.92,0:16:45.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means Akashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was trying to scare the culprit with the\Nred wall and black and white chairs nailed to the floor, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.68,0:16:47.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We don't know what the message means.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.77,0:16:50.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's one thing I don't get.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.15,0:16:59.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why did the culprit also leave the message of the red\Nwall in the room of the next victim - Naoki Shirou?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.99,0:17:05.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If they really left the message to challenge\Nthe police, were they that certain?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.58,0:17:11.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Were they that confident that the red wall\Nitself would never reveal their identity?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.04,0:17:18.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, is the culprit's motive really because of Aoi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.46,0:17:23.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe the culprit painted the wall because\Nof something pertinent to the color red.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.47,0:17:26.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, the motive was the anger caused by Aoi's death.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.97,0:17:32.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like I said, three years ago she collapsed in the\Nmansion's storage room due to a heart attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.31,0:17:36.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But her husband Akashi Shuusaku just left her there to die alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.07,0:17:39.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sound familiar?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.19,0:17:45.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's the same situation as the confined,\Nabandoned, and starved Akashi Shuusaku.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.66,0:17:47.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, that's not enough to say...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.79,0:17:49.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On the day of Aoi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s death...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.33,0:17:57.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Our three suspects and yesterday's victim, Naoki\NShirou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, all spoke with Aoi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} on the phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.55,0:18:04.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She asked, "About the portrait of me that my husband\NShuusaku made, do you guys remember where it was put?"
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.14,0:18:08.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So the thing Aoi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} tried to find in the\Nstorage room before she died was...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.60,0:18:12.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, she was looking for her portrait.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.35,0:18:20.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She also asked Shuusaku{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} about its whereabouts, but he\Ndidn't answer because he was busy finishing up his work.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.95,0:18:29.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aoi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} wanted to decorate her room\Nwith that portrait for her birthday.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.33,0:18:35.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since she died on the day before her birthday, I'm not\Nsurprised that someone would hold a grudge over this.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.75,0:18:44.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, regardless, once Koumei regains consciousness we\Ncan ask him whether he sent this "late Koumei" or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.43,0:18:48.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If he did, we could deduce its meaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.60,0:18:55.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The doctor said that if he doesn't regain consciousness\Nby tomorrow, he'll require another examination.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.98,0:18:56.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.02,0:19:00.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.36,0:19:03.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Calling you all the way out here and not letting you do much.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.94,0:19:08.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, no, I'm the one who hasn't contributed enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.16,0:19:08.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But let's face it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.78,0:19:14.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The one you really wanted to invite is\Nthis brat with glasses, isn't that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.96,0:19:20.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I thought this brat was a\Ngood choice for monitoring Koumei.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.05,0:19:26.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because once that guy puts on his thinking\Ncap, he ignores everything around him.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.26,0:19:29.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After he makes up his mind, he'd\Neven go so far as to jump off a cliff.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.51,0:19:37.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I thought even if he doesn't listen to us,\Nhe may take on candid advice from a child.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.27,0:19:41.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But he still went off by himself and ended up in trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.94,0:19:44.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Excuse me for not being useful enough...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.40,0:19:50.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, once I solve the mystery of the red\Nwall, I'll make sure to tell you first.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.33,0:19:53.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Doctor, how's my wife?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.04,0:19:57.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't worry, the operation was a success.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.83,0:19:59.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's wrong, Ran?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.13,0:20:06.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was just wondering to myself why\Nsurgical gowns have to be light green?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.76,0:20:11.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See, all those doctors and nurses wear white coats, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.35,0:20:15.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That may be true, but why are you asking this now?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.98,0:20:20.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because the case this time has something to do with colors, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.48,0:20:23.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've been thinking of colors all this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.32,0:20:25.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, I know why they're like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.73,0:20:30.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The reason why surgical gowns are light green is because\Nsurgeons constantly see blood during operations.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.20,0:20:33.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If they keep looking at it...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.78,0:20:34.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The afterimage will...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.41,0:20:37.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Interrupt their focus...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.21,0:20:47.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.51,0:20:53.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This dying message can't be acknowledged\Njust by looking at the red wall alone!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.18,0:20:58.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The message has to be interpreted by pairing\Nit with the white wall on the opposite side.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.98,0:21:01.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What happened to you two?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.77,0:21:07.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The mysterious death that occurred in the Mansion of Hope...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.44,0:21:13.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That illustrator who called that mansion home, Akashi\NShuusaku{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, was confined to his room and starved to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.66,0:21:19.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's intriguing is one of the walls was\Npainted completely red by Akashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.00,0:21:24.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Also inside the room, two chairs painted\Nwhite and black were nailed to the floor...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.38,0:21:29.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And we have Akashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} sitting on the white chair,\Nfacing the red wall, when he drew his last breath.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.63,0:21:34.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It looks like this was a dying message left by Akashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.93,0:21:41.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The murder concerns the one who died of a heart attack in this\Nmansion's storage room three years ago - Akashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.98,0:21:45.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maiden name Kobashi Aoi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, the culprit\Nmay hold a grudge over her death.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.44,0:21:48.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The case didn't end there.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.44,0:21:50.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just as we started looking into the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.11,0:21:56.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One of those who lived in the mansion, Naoki\NShirou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, was found murdered in his apartment.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.03,0:22:02.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Furthermore, his body was seated on a\Nchair, facing the closet doors painted red.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.46,0:22:09.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right - the culprit reproduced the scene\Nwhere Akashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s body was found.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.88,0:22:12.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was it a challenge to the police?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.76,0:22:18.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The suspects are among the six people who\Nresided in the mansion, three of whom still live.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.47,0:22:21.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The actor, Midorikawa Naoki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.89,0:22:25.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The fashion designer, Yamabuki Shouji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.06,0:22:29.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And CG creator, Momose Takuto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.49,0:22:34.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Akashi Shuusaku{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s dying message is...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.86,0:22:38.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Without a doubt, it's referring to that person!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.16,0:24:02.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Naoki Shirou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} said it, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.74,0:24:05.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That he would be going to Lecce in Italy soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.50,0:24:09.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, I have a great idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.08,0:24:10.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As do I.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.84,0:24:15.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why not type your strategy in one word on your\Ncell phone and then show it to each other?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.88,0:24:19.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As I expected...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.18,0:24:22.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's the Empty Fort Strategy, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.46,0:24:47.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next Conan's Hint
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.59,0:24:49.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Italy
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.64,0:24:54.89,Signs,,0,0,0,,Look forward to the Next Episode
